radiographic_examinations.findings: The dilated, fluid-filled appendix runs retrocecally along the iliac vessels in the upper pelvis. The appendix measures 1 cm at the tip with mild surrounding fat stranding and an appendicolith is visualized in the appendiceal base. Moderate colonic fecal load is noted. No focal lesions or intrahepatic biliary duct dilatation in the liver. Other abdominal organs are unremarkable.
